Core Features 
A. The Dashboard (Home) 
The central hub for the user's daily activity and motivation. 
● EliteScore Display: visualization of current points. 
● Global Rank: Real-time standing against all other users. 
● Streaks: Consecutive days of activity check-ins. 
● Basic Stats:Score Gain: Points earned in the last 7 days. 
○ Movement: Number of positions climbed or dropped on the leaderboard. 
● Active Challenge Card: Shows currently enrolled challenges, specific sub-tasks for the 
day and "Submit" buttons for deadlines. 
● Leaderboard Preview: A Top 5 snippet to keep competition visible. 
● Recommended Challenges: category-based suggestions from the library. 
B. The Challenge Concept 
Challenges are structured commitments with high stakes. 
● Library: Users browse challenges by Difficulty, Duration (e.g., 21 days), and Base Reward 
(EliteScore). 
● The Accountability Wall: Before joining, a user must invite a Spectator (friend/family) 
via email or WhatsApp link. 
○ The Spectator must click "I Agree" to be linked. 
○ The Spectator receives automated notifications of the user's Success or Failure. 
● Weekly Breakdown: Challenges are segmented by week (e.g., Python Challenge: Week 
1: Basics, Week 2: Build, Week 3: Deploy). 
● Check-ins: Users must submit "Proof of Work" twice a week. 
● Verification: Once proof is submitted and approved, the EliteScore increases. 
C. The EliteScore Economy 
The score is Public and Loud. It determines the user's reputation. 
● Starting Point: 0 EliteScore. 
● Gains (+): 
○ Daily Challenge: +20 
○ Big Challenge Completion: +50 to +100 
○ Approved Proof: Incremental gains. 
● Penalties (-): 
○ Failing/Quitting a challenge: -60 
○ Submitting wrong/fake proof: Penalty. 
○ Missing a deadline: Penalty. 
D. Leaderboard & Social 
● Beta Enrollment: All new users are automatically entered into the Beta Signup 
leaderboard. 
● Elite Access: High EliteScores unlock "Elite Challenges" that are hidden from 
lower-ranked users. 
E. User Profile 
A hybrid of a gaming profile and a professional resume. 
● Identity: Name, Username, Bio, Profile Picture. 
● Performance: EliteScore, Streak, Consistency % (on-time submissions). 
● History: Categorized list of Failed vs. Completed challenges. 
● Resume/Background: * Manual Entry: Education, Roles, Achievements, Links. 
○ AI Extraction: Upload a PDF resume to automatically populate the profile.